18/02/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- BiH Prime Minister Adnan Terzic and Macedonian President Branko Crvenkovski on Thursday (17 February) pledged co-operation in achieving their countries' common goal of Euro-Atlantic integration. 
They agreed that political and economic stability is vital to the future and prosperity of Southeast Europe. 
Later, Crvenkovski met with BiH presidency members and leading members of parliament.
In other news Thursday, Macedonian Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva visited Helsinki, where she met with Finnish President Tarja Halonen and Minister for Foreign Trade and Development Paula Lehtomaki. 
They discussed Macedonia's progress towards EU integration. 
Mitreva cited the economy, judicial reform, and fighting organised crime and corruption as the priorities. 
(FENA, PBS, RTRS, Makfax - 18/02/05; MIA, A1 TV - 17/02/05)
